  <TD CLASS="orangeblock" ROWSPAN=2 VALIGN=TOP>
    
<P>Do any other servers send mail from sbcglobal.net?</P>
<P>You can describe them by giving "arguments" to the <B>a:</B>, <B>mx:</B>, <B>ip4:</B>, and <B>ptr:</B> mechanisms.
   <B>mx:</B> takes domain names and approves all the MX servers of these domains.
   To keep the wizard short we left out <B>ptr:</B>, but it works analogously.</P>

  </TD>

  

  <TD CLASS="orangeblock" ALIGN=CENTER>
    
